      "role": "user",
      "content": "i hear u, but it feels like the \"consensus\" you're talking about assumes that these big economic gains at the top will eventually trickle down to everyone. some people argue that the wealth gap just gets wider and that the \"short term\" displacement can actually become permanent for entire communities. isn't it a bit dismissive to just label those concerns as something that's \"typically\" just a temporary phase? it feels like the benefits are being treated as a fact while the downsides are being treated as just a minor transition issue.",
